storyInfo: Despite the survival knowledge from her books being of little help in the Sargonian rainforest, Papyrus continues to explore its ecology and tribal history one step at a time.

attributes.content: She hasn't come to?
attributes.name: Calm Voice

attributes.content: Not yet, doc. The whole tribe has been waiting here all afternoon.
attributes.name: Nervous Voice

attributes.content: Hnngh...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Is anyone in a rush to see the doctor?
attributes.name: Calm Voice

attributes.content: No, we're in no rush. You should save the girl first! She's cursed!
attributes.name: Nervous Voice

attributes.content: She came from the waterfall?
attributes.name: Calm Voice

attributes.content: Yeah, that's right. I checked her front and back. She's got no rocks, and she's not hurt. She's holding a tablet she won't let go, though.
attributes.name: Nervous Voice

attributes.content: She was muttering some strange sounds in the morning, but then she quieted down.
attributes.name: Nervous Voice

attributes.content: And when I checked on her just now, it was like her breathing had stopped!
attributes.name: Nervous Voice

attributes.content: â€”Huh?! Why didn't you say that right away?
attributes.name: No Longer Calm Voice

attributes.content: If you can't save the girl, then at least help us break her curse. This is my home...
attributes.name: Nervous Voice

attributes.content: Hey, girl, can you hear me?
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: So... heavy... ugh...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Who put a heavy tablet like this on her chest?
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: Okay, I got that off you now.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: Phew!
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Good, you're responding. How do you feel?
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: I want some... mint Zubayr ice cream...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: You sure you're all better?
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: Yes, doctor. I don't have any professional medical knowledge, but... I'm well-practiced at collapsing due to heat stroke...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: *sigh* Young lady, most people don't get heat strokes in this weather. Are you ill?
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: I'm fine, physically, but I have a few questions I'd like to ask you.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Please take a look at this leaf. Is this the Beastbrain Leaf mentioned in the book that's supposed to have a cool scent and mind-refreshing properties?
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Throw that away right now.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: I don't know this Beastbrain Leaf that you speak of, but I assure you that if you grind that leaf and apply it to your forehead, you will attract acid Originium slugs!
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: Uh, okay... Th-Then, what about this fruit? Can I use it as an emergency ration for the road?
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Eat that, and you will only get a taste of the afterlife.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: What are you doing? Is that a notebook?
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: Right, this is my Tentative Travel Plan (Final Draft). It means I'm fully prepared and have made up my mind... but... I suppose now it's (Final Draft-Revised)
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Thank you very much for your advice. Do you still have any more outdoor survival tips?
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Yes.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: Just go home. There's no sightseeing to be done around here.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: Yes, I understand.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: You are sure she's all better?
attributes.name: Impetuous Villager

attributes.content: That's what she says.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: I don't think so. I still think she's cursed.
attributes.name: Impetuous Villager

attributes.content: My sister and I found her by the water this morning. She was completely out. Must've gone into the woods we're not supposed to go into.
attributes.name: Impetuous Villager

attributes.content: She kept murmuring the whole time, and she was really loud, too. Even louder than how she's talking now.
attributes.name: Impetuous Villager

attributes.content: Yes, she kept saying she was looking for some totem, some cans with guts in them... She even started ordering people around.
attributes.name: Gentle Villager

attributes.content: Exactly, I remember too! She kept muttering this one's been dead for so long and that one's been buried for years. What normal person says that?!
attributes.name: Impetuous Villager

attributes.content: Hmm...
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: If she does anything weird again, I'll cut down all the bad things, just like we cut trees!
attributes.name: Impetuous Villager

attributes.content: Relax, you two. Feeble as she is, she couldn't do anything to hurt anyone, or even get too far on her own.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: Alright, who else needs attending toâ€”
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: H-Help!
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Dear me, why are there so many slugs?!
attributes.name: Gentle Villager

attributes.content: C-C-Ca-Calm down! We're coming to help!
attributes.name: Impetuous Villager

attributes.content: I'm sorry...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Didn't I warn you that the plant attracts Originium slugs literally a minute ago?!
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: I tripped on my way out of the village...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: ...then I bumped my head into the tree and spooked the slugs under the branches. I got down on the ground and used Arts to try and protect myself, but I didn't get my aim right...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Don't push yourself like that.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: The lords ameer used to send people like you here. They'd search the wilds and take home rocks as prizes.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: What happened after that? Did they leave empty-handed?
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: How would I know? They came and went, yet life here has remained the same. The little holes they dug were instantly filled up in a single rising tide.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: If you really think you could find any kind of 'history' in this place...
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: It's okay. I'm not afraid of disappointment.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: I've made up my mind this time. Now that I've actually left home, I have to see everything here with my own eyes.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: I can decipher the text on this tablet, so I'll investigate everything based on the information written here... even if it doesn't lead to any worthwhile discoveries.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: â€”Besides, I've gathered over a hundred 'Spectacular Rainforest Tribes Sights' from my books. The forest is huge, but I should be able to see at least one, right?
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: *sigh*. Here, take these herbs. Heat stroke treatment, insect repellent, anti-emetic, even wild beast repellent... Just about everything you'll need.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: I'll be heading to another village soon. The Archosauria here are kind, but they may not be able to understand you, much less help you.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: Okay, thank you...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Right, doctor, may I ask you one more question? The villagers mentioned some kind of curse. Do you know what that is?
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Right, like this. Tie a knot around yourself with the vines, then swing it to the other side.
attributes.name: Enthusiastic Villager

attributes.content: You have to use one hand to hold the vines, though, so set down that big stone you're holding.
attributes.name: Enthusiastic Villager

attributes.content: It's okay. I can hold it under my arm.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Also, this is not a normal stone. It's inscribed with words.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: I've been collecting tablets like this one for some time now. If you find any like it, please do bring them to me. I can pay you for them.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Stones with words on them? I've heard about them.
attributes.name: Enthusiastic Villager

attributes.content: Really? From whom? May I talk to them?
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Well, he's been lying under the ground for a while now. That's what you get for going to the cursed forest. We don't even know if he's worth pitying.
attributes.name: Enthusiastic Villager

attributes.content: I figured. All the tablets that could be monuments are placed right at the edge of that forest...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: What were you saying?
attributes.name: Enthusiastic Villager

attributes.content: N-Nothing. I'm asking if you could help swing me over to the shore on the other side.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: No problem! One, two, let's goâ€”
attributes.name: Enthusiastic Villager

attributes.content: Wraaaaaaggghhhhâ€”
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Hold on! My tablet! I'm going to drop itâ€”
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Don't let go! Don't grabâ€”
attributes.name: Enthusiastic Villager

attributes.content: H-Helpâ€”ugh...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Papyrus, you're back! You were gone for so long, I thought you'd leftâ€”
attributes.name: Gentle Villager

attributes.content: Dear me, why are you all drenched again? Had another fall in the water?
attributes.name: Gentle Villager

attributes.content: N-No... It was the rain... Achoo!
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Izaja, register this tablet... Right, the weather forecast tablet that other tribe gave me. Not that knowing it'd rain would help me at all...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Mm... Izaja... Why are you just standing there, not working?
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: W-Who are you talking to?
attributes.name: Gentle Villager

attributes.content: â€”Oh no, you're not Izaja!
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Sorry, please forget whatever I just said...! There's no other tribe! I-I was just... Ah...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: â€”You're burning up. No wonder you're talking nonsense.
attributes.name: Gentle Villager

attributes.content: *sigh*... No more talk of curses. Poor thing. Let's head back inside and get some rest.
attributes.name: Gentle Villager

attributes.content: Once you're feeling better, I'll tell you which tree oil you can put on your clothes to waterproof them and keep Originium slugs from climbing up your legs.
attributes.name: Gentle Villager

attributes.content: Thanks...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Silly girl, I don't understand why you keep thanking people. I didn't put the trees there, I'm just telling you how to use them.
attributes.name: Gentle Villager

attributes.content: After I tell you, you can go tell the next person who could use the knowledge.
attributes.name: Gentle Villager

attributes.content: Alright, let's go.
attributes.name: Gentle Villager

attributes.content: Papyrus, why are trying to chop a tree? You need strength for work like this. Can I help?
attributes.name: Stout Villager

attributes.content: *gasp*... *gasp*... No thanks... I'm fine...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: I just wanted to see if this Arts-powered chainsaw could really save some strength...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: That looks amazing! Can I try?
attributes.name: Stout Villager

attributes.content: Of course! Just let me figure out how to turn it off first...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Uh, hold on. Papyrus? Don't make that thing spin so fast! You're facing it the wrong way!
attributes.name: Stout Villager

attributes.content: Out of the way!
attributes.name: Stout Villager

attributes.content: S-Sorry...!
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Haha! I knew it! Every time you head out, you bring back some really useful toys!
attributes.name: Stout Villager

attributes.content: R-Right... Anyway, I'll make sure your roof gets fixed...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Whoa, this is good!
attributes.name: Impetuous Villager

attributes.content: Hold on... That tablet isn't for frying fowlbeast eggs...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: You just want to look at the drawings, right? I'll clean it up before giving it back.
attributes.name: Impetuous Villager

attributes.content: Okay...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Are you not worried about the curse anymore?
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: What's there to worry about? You've got plenty of those tablets and you're still fine. I even checked on my grandma's graveâ€”if she hasn't crawled back out, then it means nothing bad has happened.
attributes.name: Impetuous Villager

attributes.content: Has she... crawled out before?
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Never, haha! You know, I'm a really lucky guy.
attributes.name: Impetuous Villager

attributes.content: Eh, that reminds me, Papyrus. How come I haven't ever heard you tell any stories about yourself?
attributes.name: Impetuous Villager

attributes.content: I told you about the tree that made the spear I used to kill my first prey, but you haven't shared where you come from, how big your tribe is, or how many fistfights you've won...
attributes.name: Impetuous Villager

attributes.content: I... I don't have anything interesting to talk about.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: I didn't spend much time with people my age, and I rarely had a chance to step outside my family's manor. All I had in my life was books.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Oh, books! What books do the traders there sell? I love the ones that are all pictures!
attributes.name: Impetuous Villager

attributes.content: No, I'm afraid it's not quite what you're thinking...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: I come from a family of academics, so we have a large collection of treasured literature at home that is maintained and expanded by each generation.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Of course, we have books on a variety of topics, but like many people in our city, my father thinks history is the most noble of knowledge.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: As for myself... I'm not sure if I like it or just got used to it because I had no other choice. I might be more familiar with how people lived two thousand years ago than my own life.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Two thousand? Whoa, that's like my grandmother's grandmother's grandmother's...
attributes.name: Impetuous Villager

attributes.content: I don't even know how far back it goes! It sounds like you know lots of really fun things, Papyrus!
attributes.name: Impetuous Villager

attributes.content: Fun things...? Right, there used to be a small number of scholars who speculated that the Manticores were the lords of the rainforest, idols worshiped by all.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: They pointed to a skeleton found in a massive tomb as evidence, but later, more advanced technology proved that they were simply too creative when they put the skeleton back together.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: They put the bones back together in the wrong spots, and made an Archosauria look like a Manticore.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Speaking of Archosauria, there's also an especially famous 'entertainment hypothesis'.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: The reason that the Archosauria did not leave any traces in early recorded history is that their intelligence and technology had already developed to a level that was far beyond modern Sargon's.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: They had already more than satisfied their curiosity, and so they didn't want any contact with the outside world and intentionally erased all traces of any explorers who found them.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: And also...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: ...Oh, I'm sorry! Once I get into my area of expertise, I tend to go on and on, even if I'm just having a laugh.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: What's there to be sorry about? You were telling us a bunch of things we didn't know. It's fun.
attributes.name: Gentle Villager

attributes.content: Right, every time I hear you say those strange words, it just pulls me in, like I'm possessed!
attributes.name: Stout Villager

attributes.content: Ahem... Okay, that was all just academic anecdotes. Whether you understand them or not, please don't take them seriously...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: But there's really not much more I can tell besides the stories in my books.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Before I made up my mind to leave home and go on a journey, I had left Menat-Ha'mait, where I was born and raised, only once.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Keep going!
attributes.name: Impetuous Villager

attributes.content: Okay... One day, I had an argument with a friend over some documents. She suddenly slammed on the desk, and said she was taking me to a mutual friend to reason things out.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Maybe we were both too agitated, but we didn't even think of trying the professors at the academy... She contacted a caravan, and we left with them.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: At first, I was really scared that my father would find out and punish me for wasting time and putting myself in danger.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: But actually, we ended up staying in a carriage compartment that was made to be like a bedroom. I kept following my routine and woke up at seven in the morning to keep working on my thesis.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Our mutual friend rushed to the closest town to meet up with us as well.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: The only things I remember about our meeting are her taking some scary photos of a tomb excavation site from unexpected angles for me...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: And the weather being so terrible that I kept the window shut the entire trip.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: I know that was the right decision for my health, but I still wonder what it looked like outside the window.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: The tribespeople all stare at each other, apparently not expecting the story to end so abruptly.
After a brief moment, right after somebody slurps a fowlbeast egg, one of the audience members breaks the silence.
I've got a question. What's a compartment? How did it bring your whole room with you?
attributes.name: Impetuous Villager

attributes.content: That reminds me, I also wanted to ask, what's an academy?
attributes.name: Gentle Villager

attributes.content: Papyrus finds herself surrounded by the Archosauria and bombarded with questions.
Some are ones that she had anticipated, while others are questions that she had never thought about.
From the library of her childhood home to the magnificent Varjavandabad Museum and then the Rhodes Island landship...
As she answers the questions, her boring life slowly sounds more vivid and colorful.
Finally, everyone asks her about her current trip.
I still have one more question, Papyrus. You keep on bringing all those strange trinkets, like saws and stones that tell when it'll rain... Where did you get them?
attributes.name: Impetuous Villager

attributes.content: Louder! We're here to make friends! We need to be passionate, and more passionate than the other side!
attributes.name: Enthusiastic Voice

attributes.content: We'll shout the slogan Papyrus taught us! Nothing will go wrong!
attributes.name: Enthusiastic Voice

attributes.content: 'Make friends', eh? Young lady, the villagers outside are mobilizing to enter the forbidden zone. That was all your idea, wasn't it?
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: I thought you'd have left by now.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: If I hadn't gotten sick or collapsed from exhaustion so much, I definitely would've left...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: I'm sorry about the disagreement we had, doctor.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Looks like you didn't heed my advice.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: I just think that if the curse doesn't exist, then the other side of the rainforest they're so afraid of is just another tribe. They shouldn't be trapped by their ancestors' legends.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: You insist on revealing the 'true history', even if it means hurting the ones who are alive.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: No... I've thought it over. Please let me explain.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Just as you said, I can't be sure what will happen when the two tribes make contact. There has been much bloodshed between tribes throughout history.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: That's why I've been going between the two tribes in order to compare and contrast them.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: If they once had a close relationship and still share common rituals, then the two sides would already have the foundation of a friendly encounter.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Uh, but actually... it was the inventions of the other tribes I've been bringing back that piqued their curiosity. Both sides proactively asked to meet their friends on the other side of the forest.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: So this was not your idea.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: Right. Thinking back, perhaps I was just playing the role of a Messenger.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Oh, doctor, they're planning to build a bridge by the waterfall. Maybe you won't have to take a detour through the foggiest part of the rainforest the next time you leave.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: What about you?
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: You're a strange young lady. You could've come to this place in those air-conditioned metal monsters like those heralds of the lords ameer.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: I can tell your social standing is even higher than theirs. You could've had someone dig up the history between these two tribes for you.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: It is within your power to interfere in their lives by sending a Messenger to demand the two tribes form ties or even merge into one. I've seen that happen many times.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: Why put yourself through all this trouble?
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: Because I didn't want to come here for sightseeing... I want to know what it looks like outside the window.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Before I left home, someone I really respected once told me to discover the meaning of my journey for myself, and that I should never forget it, but also not think too highly of it.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: That's why I tried my hardest. Although going by the results, I guess the only thing that I've gained so far is a whole lot of nightmares...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: But I think it's much better to have nightmares every time I see Originium slugs than to touch them curiously in the office before heading back to the desk to document with joy.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: You really are a weird one.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: Are you happy, after suffering through all that?
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: Truth is... I do miss the air conditioning and purified water back in the office, and all the books and resources readily available.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Every day, I feel just how insignificant each one of my steps is compared to Sargon's long history.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: My father is right in that regard. Compared to my research, the weeks I've spent in this rainforest are all a waste of time.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: I was only able to persevere and stay here for such a long time because I wanted to finish one thing.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Those tablets.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: Right.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: You taught the locals a slogan. Looks like you got plenty of information out of those tablets.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: Actually... those tablets only talk about their exploits and feats in battle.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Just as you predicted, the Archosauria are born combative. In the past, the two tribes often came to blows whenever they saw each other.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: I think... it's because somebody would go missing every time they went to the other side that the tribes slowly got the idea that the forest curses people.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: But I suppose the truth of the past doesn't really matter to the people alive right now, does it?
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Very well... I'll keep that secret for you, and I'll keep an eye on the tribes so they don't come to blows again after you leave.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: We'll call it my thanks to you for getting them to build this bridge and saving me some time in the future.
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: Thank you so much... Uh, if you wouldn't mind bringing me with you when you left this time, that'd be even better.
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: I want to make it to the closest town in one piece and enjoy an ice-cold glass of fruit juice before contacting the Rhodes Island office... I'll pay!
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Not standing by your principles anymore?
attributes.name: Roaming Doctor

attributes.content: Th-That's because I'm leaving!
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: Besides, now that the tribesmen are finally uniting and heading into the forest that they were so afraid of, in hopes of making new friends, I've finally realized...
attributes.name: Papyrus

attributes.content: In the end, the most important thing is taking that very first step.
attributes.name: Papyrus
